HEADWORD: Cippus
<hw>Cip"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cippi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., stake, post.]</ety>
<def>A small, low pillar, square or round, commonly having an
inscription, used by the ancients for various purposes, as for
indicating the distances of places, for a landmark, for sepulchral
inscriptions, etc.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

